						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Bṛihadīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōnēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ year lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription may be assigned to the 12th-13th century on palaeographical grounds. The extant details of date available is 152nd day of the king's reign period.</p>						

						<p>It records an order of the king issued to the priests <hi rend="italic">(mūlappaṭṭuḍaippañchāchārya)</hi></p>						

						</summary>
